So from what I’ve gathered about Big Sky, the etymology of such a nation is quite literal in its meaning, as it references the open, beautiful skies of Montana which is quite known for its natural beauty. There seems to be a trend for the Montanan population to name their state to accurately depict its environmental features while also treading in the dangerous territory of how names could end up being seen as claims to certain pacts of land. I assume the logic behind the naming of Big Sky is because of the fact that no one can truly ‘claim’ the sky.

Looking over at Darien, I realize just how much of a hotbed world politics is in ASDT’s world, mainly due to the fact that in this world, there is a point of divergence where Europe has its own agenda and isn’t in the same umbrella as the US. What a mess but with so many parties involved in South America, I can imagine there to be no shortage of opportunity for warfare and political friction to thrive in. I can’t imagine that any authority in Southern and Central America would last long without having its authority challenged by the pawns of the world’s superpower. Darien remains strong by being an alliance between a civilian government and a criminal syndicate. It’s funny to see them have such a cooperative and beneficial agreement with one another, exploiting the world’s chaos in a realistic fashion that seems to help Darien stay afloat in the best way possible, although of course, there’s always a catch when allying with criminals.
